SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 939
By Massey
A RESOLUTION to recognize and congratulate the Home Builders
Association of Greater Knoxville on the occasion
of its seventy-fifth anniversary.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that this General Assembly should pay tribute to those exemplary
institutions that work with purpose and conviction to improve the quality of life in their respective
communities; and
WHEREAS, the Home Builders Association of Greater Knoxville (HBAGK) is one such
outstanding organization; and
WHEREAS, established in 1951, HBAGK has served for seventy-five years as a vital
voice for the construction and home building industry in East Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, today, HBAGK is composed of more than five hundred members
representing a broad cross section of the building industry, including builders, remodelers,
trades contractors, carpenters, bricklayers, building materials suppliers, bankers, attorneys,
insurance professionals, and numerous other related professions; and
WHEREAS, through this diverse membership, the association brings together
professionals from across the home building and construction industry who work collaboratively
to support the growth and success of the housing sector in East Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, HBAGK actively represents the interests of the building community through
education, advocacy, and community involvement, maintaining an open line of communication
with elected officials and governmental agencies whose policies affect the home building
industry; and
WHEREAS, HBAGK's Governmental Affairs Committee continuously monitors building
and legislative issues affecting the home building industry and maintains communication with
elected officials and government agencies whose actions impact its members' businesses; and
SJR0939
015459
- 1 -

WHEREAS, HBAGK serves a wide region of East Tennessee, including Anderson,
Blount, Campbell, Claiborne, Cocke, Fentress, Grainger, Hamblen, Jefferson, Knox, Loudon,
Monroe, Morgan, Roane, Scott, Sevier, and Union counties; and
WHEREAS, membership in HBAGK also includes membership in the Home Builders
Association of Tennessee and the National Association of Home Builders, connecting local
professionals to a broader network of industry leadership and resources; and
WHEREAS, guided by its mission to represent and promote the home building industry
through education, advocacy, and community involvement, HBAGK continues to play a
significant role in creating neighborhoods and opportunities for future generations of
Tennesseans; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we specially recognize HBAGK for its many years of
dedicated service to the construction industry and to the people of East Tennessee; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we recognize and congratulate the Home Builders
Association of Greater Knoxville on the occasion of its seventy-fifth anniversary and commend
its members for their dedication to promoting quality housing, responsible development, and the
economic well-being of the communities they serve.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
